observations.recommendation:
1. The Inventory Committee follow the procedures prescribed in the one-time cleansing of PPE and ensure the updating of Property Cards by posting all unrecorded acquisition/receipt, issue/transfer, and disposal of PPE;
2. The Inventory Committee to prepare the list of PPEs found at station and provide property cards, make a list of missing/non-existing PPEs, and observe the procedures for the disposition of said properties;
3. The Accounting Unit to take up accounting entries to recognize PPE found at station and its losses, and set-up the corresponding receivables from the concerned accountable officer/personnel and update the PPELC/SL and ensure the total balance of PPELCs/SLs tally with the balances of controlling PPE accounts in the General Ledger; and
4. The Inventory Committee and Accounting Unit to reconcile their records in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We recommended that the Municipality adhere strictly with the Civil Service Commission guidelines on the grant of PRAISE. Likewise, complete supporting documents should be observed by submitting the following:
a) Copy of the composition of the PRAISE Committee;
b) Copy of the Municipality’s CSC – Approved PRAISE;
c) Performance Ratings of each permanent officers and employees;
d) Basis for the amount given;
e) Criteria in granting the PRAISE Bonus as recommended by the PRAISE Committee;
f) List of Savings and Monetary Awards earned / generated during CY 2015 and relevant supporting documents;
g) Evaluation reports or any documentation recognizing the productivity, creativeness, innovation made/or ethical behavior of employees or group of employees making them eligible for the PRAISE; and
h) Specific legal basis which allows the grant of the incentives in the absence of the above requirements, otherwise the incentives granted be refunded immediately.

